---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, PROFILE_IMAGE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="About Me | Victor Zhang" description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="about-page">
			<div class="container">
				<img src={PROFILE_IMAGE} alt="Victor Zhang" class="about-profile-image" />
				
				<h1>About Me</h1>
				
				<p>
					<strong>Mobile &amp; Systems Engineer</strong> with 7 years of experience building and shipping production apps across the US, Canada, and China.
				</p>

				<p>
					I specialize in <strong>end-to-end, data-driven mobile systems</strong>—from <strong>real-time ingestion and synchronization</strong> (e.g., BLE streaming via CoreBluetooth, local persistence, and cloud sync) to <strong>backend services and telemetry pipelines</strong>. I design systems that handle long-running sessions and unreliable networks, with a focus on <strong>correctness, concurrency, and reliability</strong>.
				</p>

				<p>
					I approach systems through <strong>data flow, control policies, state, and rendering</strong>—for example, designing caching strategies (TTL, invalidation), retry with exponential backoff, and sync behavior under intermittent connectivity, then transforming streamed data into consistent UI state and responsive interfaces.
				</p>

				<p>
					I’m comfortable going deep on <strong>iOS native</strong> when system-level understanding is required, and I also work effectively in <strong>React Native</strong> when cross-platform leverage makes sense. I regularly work across the stack—from device integration and client architecture to backend services (Node.js, FastAPI, Redis) and production observability—to ensure systems remain reliable in practice.
				</p>

				<h2>Vibe Coding Workflow</h2>
				<section class="agent-harness-card" aria-labelledby="agent-harness-title">
					<div>
						<p class="eyebrow">Solo dev agent harness</p>
						<h3 id="agent-harness-title">Budget-aware orchestration, not agent sprawl.</h3>
						<p>
							I use git-native worktrees and task contracts to coordinate Claude, Codex, and other coding agents without losing handoff context. The key idea is lightweight: plan with a strong model, execute inside explicit file boundaries, verify deterministically, then review fewer, higher-quality branches.
						</p>
						<div class="harness-links">
							<a href="/blog/beyond-worktrees-budget-aware-multi-agent-coding-harness/">Read the workflow</a>
							<a class="wtcraft-link" href="https://github.com/zywkloo/wtcraft">View <span>wtcraft</span></a>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="handoff-diagram" aria-label="Planner to contract to executor workflow">
						<div class="diagram-node">
							<span>Planner</span>
							<small>Claude</small>
						</div>
						<div class="diagram-arrow">handoff</div>
						<div class="diagram-node diagram-node-contract">
							<span>Task Contract</span>
							<small>Scope / Off-limits / Verify</small>
						</div>
						<div class="diagram-arrow">bounded work</div>
						<div class="diagram-node">
							<span>Executor</span>
							<small>Codex</small>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>
				<h2>Recent Experience</h2>
				<div class="experience-item">
					<h3>Mobile Engineer &amp; Platform Developer - Medico Supplies INC.</h3>
					<p class="experience-date">Mar 2025 - Present</p>
					<ul>
						<li>- Architected and built a health analytics backend using Python, FastAPI, Redis, and async task queues for long-session physiological data processing, reliable live mobile ingestion, telemetry pipelines, and scalable caching policies</li>
						<li>- Developed a React Native app with TypeScript and local persistence, while owning native Swift/Kotlin modules for BLE parsing, sync, concurrency-sensitive device workflows, and mobile system integration</li>
						<li>- Delivered a Windows desktop 3D scanning application with C#/.NET and C++ interop, optimizing mesh pipelines for clinical-grade accuracy</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="experience-item">
					<h3>Senior Mobile / Frontend Engineer - NinjaTech AI</h3>
					<p class="experience-date">Oct 2024 - Jan 2025</p>
					<ul>
						<li>- Contributed to MyNinja.ai Agentic App powered by fine-tuned Llama LLM across web and mobile — developed React.js features with RTK Query for CRUD, Tailwind CSS styling, and AI-generated image state management.</li>
						<li>- Developed React Native mobile app with TypeScript, Expo Router, Zod validation, implementing parallel mixed-content message streaming with Zustand (MVVM), achieving 60fps scrolling for Markdown citations and research cards.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<h2>Key Achievements</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>🎯 Founding mobile engineer on a Canada-based ed-tech startup app launch, contributing iOS-native depth while also shipping React Native features that supported fundraising in early 2023</li>
					<li>🎮 Game Design Lead for a title that reached #1 in Sports in China on May 3, 2015, as a founding game designer helping a startup grow from pre-seed to IPO</li>
					<li>🥇 2x Hackathon Winner (CuHacking 2019 &amp; 2020)</li>
					<li>🏆 Carleton University Medal in Computer Science</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Background</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>💻 7 years of software engineering experience focused on mobile products, backend services, and reliable system design at scale</li>
					<li>🎯 iOS-native and cross-platform mobile delivery experience with startups across the US, Canada, and China</li>
					<li>🎮 4 years in mobile game design, from concept to App Store launch</li>
					<li>📺 Live coding streamer on twitch.tv/zywkloo, covering coding contests and gaming</li>
					<li>💡 Passionate about building scalable applications and mentoring developers</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Education</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>📖 Master of Data Science, UBC, Vancouver, Canada</li>
					<li>🍁 B.Sc. in Computer Science, Carleton University, Ottawa, Canada</li>
					<li>🏙️ B.Eng. in Urban Planning, Peking University, Beijing, China</li>
					<li>🥇 Carleton University Medal in Computer Science (Fall 2020)</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>How I Decompose Mobile Systems</h2>
				<p>
					I usually break mobile systems into a few practical layers so I can reason clearly about performance, consistency, reliability, and scalability end to end.
				</p>
				<div class="design-grid">
					<div class="design-card">
						<h3>1. Data Plane</h3>
						<p>Execution paths that move data through the system: BLE streams, API calls, parsing, persistence, uploads, downloads, and live pipelines.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="design-card">
						<h3>2. Control Policies</h3>
						<p>Rules that shape behavior: caching and invalidation, retry and backoff, auth, feature flags, rate limits, and sync strategy.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="design-card">
						<h3>3. State Management</h3>
						<p>How raw data becomes consistent UI state through ViewModels, observable streams, and single sources of truth.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="design-card">
						<h3>4. Rendering</h3>
						<p>The presentation layer where SwiftUI, UIKit, or React Native turn state into responsive, smooth user experiences.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="design-card">
						<h3>5. Orchestration</h3>
						<p>Workflow coordination across the stack: connect, ingest, store, sync, notify, and recover without tangling responsibilities.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="design-card">
						<h3>6. Infrastructure</h3>
						<p>The SDKs and services underneath the product: CoreBluetooth, URLSession, Firebase, AWS, databases, queues, and platform tooling.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="design-card">
						<h3>7. Observability</h3>
						<p>Production visibility through logging, metrics, analytics, telemetry, and feedback loops that keep systems measurable and trustworthy.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<h2>Technologies I Work With</h2>
				<div class="tech-grid">
					<div class="tech-category">
						<h3>Mobile</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Swift / SwiftUI</li>
							<li>UIKit</li>
							<li>React Native</li>
							<li>Core Data</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="tech-category">
						<h3>Backend</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Python / FastAPI</li>
							<li>Node.js / Express</li>
							<li>Redis / Queues</li>
							<li>Postgres / MongoDB</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="tech-category">
						<h3>Frontend / Desktop</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>React</li>
							<li>Next.js</li>
							<li>macOS (SwiftUI)</li>
							<li>Windows (.NET / C#)</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="tech-category">
						<h3>Systems / Tools</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>C# / .NET</li>
							<li>C++ / CMake</li>
							<li>Docker / AWS</li>
							<li>Git / CI/CD</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.about-page {
		padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5.5rem) 0;
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 820px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1.5rem;
	}

	.about-profile-image {
		width: 128px;
		height: 128px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		object-fit: cover;
		margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
		display: block;
		border: 4px solid var(--surface-raised);
		box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--line), var(--shadow-md);
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		text-align: center;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.9rem);
		margin-top: 3.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
	}

	p {
		font-size: 1.075rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	p strong {
		color: var(--accent-dark);
	}

	ul {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
	}

	ul li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	.agent-harness-card {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: 1.35rem;
		margin: 1.25rem 0 2.5rem;
		padding: clamp(1.35rem, 3vw, 1.8rem);
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		background:
			linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.08), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.88)),
			var(--surface-raised);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	.agent-harness-card h3 {
		font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.55rem);
		margin: 0.35rem 0 0.75rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	.agent-harness-card p {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.harness-links {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		margin-top: 1.2rem;
	}

	.harness-links a {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: var(--surface-raised);
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.18);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.harness-links .wtcraft-link {
		background: var(--accent);
		color: #fff;
		border-color: transparent;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-accent);
	}

	.harness-links .wtcraft-link:hover {
		background: var(--accent-dark);
		color: #fff;
		transform: translateY(-1px);
	}

	.wtcraft-link span {
		margin-left: 0.28rem;
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 1.05em;
		letter-spacing: 0.01em;
	}

	.handoff-diagram {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.65rem;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: calc(var(--radius) - 4px);
		background: var(--surface-deep);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
		box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
	}

	.diagram-node {
		padding: 0.85rem 0.95rem;
		border-radius: 10px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.09);
	}

	.diagram-node span,
	.diagram-node small {
		display: block;
	}

	.diagram-node span {
		color: #f8fafc;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.diagram-node small {
		margin-top: 0.2rem;
		color: #a5b4fc;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
	}

	.diagram-node-contract {
		background: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.22);
		border-color: rgba(165, 180, 252, 0.34);
	}

	.diagram-arrow {
		color: #cbd5e1;
		font-size: 0.76rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.design-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 1.75rem 0 2.5rem;
	}

	.design-card {
		background: var(--surface-raised);
		padding: 1.4rem 1.5rem;
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
		transition: transform 0.25s var(--ease), box-shadow 0.25s var(--ease);
	}
	.design-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-3px);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	.design-card h3 {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
	}

	.design-card p {
		font-size: 0.97rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin-bottom: 0;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	@media (min-width: 768px) {
		.design-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}

		.agent-harness-card {
			grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.25fr) minmax(260px, 0.75fr);
			align-items: center;
		}
	}

	.tech-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: 1.25rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	@media (min-width: 640px) {
		.tech-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}
	}

	@media (min-width: 1000px) {
		.tech-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
		}
	}

	.tech-category {
		background: var(--surface-raised);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
	}

	.tech-category h3 {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		letter-spacing: 0.01em;
	}

	.tech-category ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.97rem;
	}

	.tech-category li {
		padding: 0.5rem 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	.tech-category li:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	.experience-item {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		padding: 1.6rem;
		background: var(--surface-raised);
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		border: 1px solid var(--line);
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
	}

	.experience-item h3 {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}

	.experience-date {
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		color: var(--accent);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		font-style: normal;
	}

	.experience-item ul {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
</style>
